<p><b>What is the difference between Kierkegaard and Kant?</b> For Kant, the primacy of the practical reason leaves no special room for divine duties that are not ethical at the same time. On the other hand, Kierkegaard's defence of the sacrifice is orbiting around the possibility of a teleological suspension of the ethical.</p>
